Class PrintingHistoryService

java.lang.Object
spss.project.backend.history.printing.PrintingHistoryService
@Service public class PrintingHistoryService extends Object
This class provides methods for interacting with the printing history of the students. The printing history is stored in a MongoDB database and can be accessed using the methods of this class.

  • Method Details

    • save

      public PrintingHistoryItem save(String studentId, String printerId, String documentId, PaperSize paperSize, List<Integer> pageNumbers, int numberOfCopies, boolean singleSided, LocalDateTime timeOrdered, LocalDateTime timePrinted, boolean successful) throws Exception
      Saves a printing history item in the database.
      Parameters:
      studentId - the id of the student who printed the document
      printerId - the id of the printer on which the document was printed
      documentId - the id of the document which was printed
      paperSize - the size of the paper the document was printed on
      pageNumbers - the page numbers of the document which were printed
      numberOfCopies - the number of copies of the document which were printed
      singleSided - whether the document was printed single or double sided
      timeOrdered - the time at which the printing job was requested
      timePrinted - the time at which the printing job was completed
      successful - whether the printing job was successful
      Returns:
      the saved printing history item
      Throws:
      Exception - if an error occurs while saving the printing history item

    • getPrinterPrintingHistory

      public List<PrintingHistoryItem> getPrinterPrintingHistory(String printerId, LocalDateTime from, LocalDateTime to) throws Exception
      Finds all printing history items which were printed on the given printer between the given times.
      Parameters:
      printerId - the id of the printer on which the printing jobs were printed
      from - the start time of the range (inclusive)
      to - the end time of the range (inclusive)
      Returns:
      a list of all printing history items which were printed on the given printer between the given times, sorted by the time at which the printing jobs were completed in descending order
      Throws:
      Exception - if an error occurs while retrieving the printing history items
